title: Name Released Of Man Killed In Semi Collision Near Bridgewater
text:
Name Released Of Man Killed In Semi Collision Near Bridgewater October 17, 2015, 10:47 AM BRIDGEWATER, SD - 
South Dakota Highway Patrol has released the name of the man killed in a collision with a semi-truck near Bridgewater, SD Friday afternoon. 
Twenty-eight-year-old Benjamin Tollefson of Parkston died when his truck crossed the center lane going westbound on SD Highway 42 and struck a semi-truck driven by 26-year-old Matthew Geidel. 
Tollefson died of his injuries. Geidel was not hurt. Both men were wearing seatbelts. Authorities say the investigation of the incident is ongoing. Â© 2015 KELOLAND TV. All Rights Reserved.
